      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Price of Stopping Terrorists</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Alex Stein letter holds there is 'simply no excuse' for security lapse in bombing of United States destroyer Cole (Oct 17 editorial)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Yemenis Now Say That Ship Blast Was Criminal Act'' (front page, Oct. 17):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Yemenis Now Say That Ship Blast Was Criminal Act'' (front page, Oct. 17):</p>
        <p>There is simply no excuse for the security lapse in the bombing of the United States destroyer Cole. Can we not expect a little bit of common sense by somebody in the vast army of security experts who live on our tax dollars? Congress should investigate.</p>
        <p>ALEX STEIN  Secaucus, N.J., Oct. 17, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
